{"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/Helperlink","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/TrailingAction"],"anchor":"Structures","title":"Structures"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/init(label:text:placeholder:prefix:suffix:leadingIcon:flipLeadingIcon:trailingAction:helperText:helperLink:isOutlined:status:)"],"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/body"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/Status","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/Style"],"anchor":"Enumerations","title":"Enumerations"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput\/View-Implementations"],"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Structure","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSTextInput","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSTextInput","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"platforms":[{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"15.0"},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"15.0"},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"visionOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"}],"role":"symbol","title":"OUDSTextInput","externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents13OUDSTextInputV","symbolKind":"struct"},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudstextinput"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSTextInput","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSTextInput"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"],"kind":"mentions"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It provides a visual and interactive affordance for text entry while supporting labels, placeholders, icons and helper messages.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Layout","anchor":"Layout","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Text input is based on several configurable UI elements:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"label","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": It is used to describe the purpose of the input."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In some UI contexts, especially when space is limited or when the input is part of a compact layout (search bars, filters, inline forms), the label can be hidden."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, hiding the label should only be done if the purpose of the input remains clear thanks to a placeholder or contextual icon"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and if the label is still accessible to screen readers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Hiding a label is a design choice that must balance visual simplicity and clarity of intent, without compromising inclusiveness or form guidance."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"placeholder","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": if the text of the text input is empty a placeholder provides a hint or guidance inside the field to suggest expected input."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A prefix and a suffix can be added to give more context."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"leading icon","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": it helps indicate the purpose of the input (magnifying glass for search, envelope for email, phone device for phone number)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Only use a leading icon if it adds clear functional or contextual value."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"trailing action","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": it is used to provide actions related to the field: clear input, toggle password visibility, open a date picker, etc."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Can also indicate status or feedback (error checkmark, loading spinner)."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Outlined style","anchor":"Outlined-style","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"By ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"text":", the input is with a subtle background fill and invisible bottom border, creating a softer and more contained look.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Best suited for dense layouts or to enhance visibility.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"outlined"}]},{"text":", the text input is a minimalist design with a transparent background and a visible stroke outlining the field.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This style may be interesting for contexts other than form pages:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When inputs need to feel lightweight and unobtrusive"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a header (search field)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a selection\/filtering feature in a product catalog"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["   \/\/ An outlined text input","   OUDSTextInput(label: \"Label\", text: $text, isOutlined: true)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Rounded layout","anchor":"Rounded-layout","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Text input can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To activate the rounded button behavior, set to true the ","type":"text"},{"code":"hasRoundedTextInputs","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Tuning","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like ","type":"text"},{"code":"SoshTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"WireframeTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Status","anchor":"Status","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Five status are proposed for all layouts:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Default neutral appearance, whether empty or filled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It allows users to click, focus, and type freely without restrictions."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"error","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": The "},{"code":"error","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" status indicates that the user input does not meet validation rules or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"expected formatting. It provides immediate visual feedback, typically through a red border,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"error icon, and a clear, accessible error message positioned below the input. The error messages replaces the helper text."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"loading","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": The "},{"code":"loading","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" state indicates that the system is processing or retrieving data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"related to the text entered. A progress indicator appears to inform the user that an action is in progress."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"readOnly","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" :The"},{"code":"readOnly","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", lets the text visible but not editable"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"disabled","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": In "},{"code":"disabled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" status, the field is non-interactive and grayed out to indicate it cannot be changed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note the SwiftUI "},{"code":"View.disabled()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is ignored."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Helpers","anchor":"Helpers","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Helper text","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":":  A supporting text conveys additional information about the input field,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as how it will be used. It should ideally only take up a single line, though may wrap"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to multiple lines if required, and be either persistently visible or visible only on focus."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Helper link","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": If the helper text is not sufficient, it’s possible to offer the user"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an additional help link (the link can be external or open a modal)."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Accessibility considerations","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"By default no haptics are done by the component for the trailing action.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However you should think about cases wher you will have to make the devices vibrates.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can refer to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/design\/human-interface-guidelines\/playing-haptics","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Mandatory field indication","anchor":"Mandatory-field-indication","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If all fields are mandatory (several fields present): display the message “All fields are mandatory” at the top of your formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Do not use an asterisk at the end of each field label, nor the word “mandatory.”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If not all fields are mandatory (several fields present): display the message “All fields marked with an * are mandatory” at the top of your formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use an asterisk (*) at the end of each mandatory field label, and ensures this is well vocalized.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"UI rendering of the asterisk must be done with ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"fbold font weight"}]},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative content color"}]},{"text":" (red-.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the mention “(optional)” at the end of each optional field label. Note that this rule is not systematic, it remains an option, to be used if needed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If there is only one field in the formular, or if the mandatory nature is obvious (such as login\/password),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"no mention is necessary since the fields are essential to the formular’s functionality.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ The text to display and edit","    @State var text: String = \"\"","","    \/\/ Empty text and no placeholder","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text)","","    \/\/ Empty text with placeholder and suffix","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, placeholder: \"firstName.lastName\", suffix: \"@orange.com\")","","    \/\/ Empty text with prefix and suffix","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, prefix: \"Distance\", suffix: \"km\")","","    \/\/ Add a leading icon for more context","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, placeholder: \"firstName.lastName\", suffix: \"@orange.com\", leadingIcon: Image(systemName: \"envelope\"))","","    \/\/ Add a trailing button with local image namde \"ic_cross\" for additional action","    let trailingAction = OUDSTextInput.TrailingAction(icon: Image(\"ic_cross\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Delete\") { text = \"\" }","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\", text: $text, trailingAction: trailingAction)","","    \/\/ With helper text","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Email\",","                  text: $text,","                  placeholder: \"firstName.lastName\",","                  suffix: \"@orange.com\",","                  helperText: \"The email will be automatically completed with @orange.com\")","","    \/\/ With helper link","    @Environment(\\.openURL) private var openUrl","","    let helperLink = OUDSTextInput.HelperLink(text: \"Helper Link\") {","       openUrl.callAsFunction(url)","    }","","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Label\", text: $text, placeholder: \"Placeholder\", helperLink: helperLink)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSTextInput(label: \"Label\", text: $text, flipLeadingIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/unified-design-system.orange.com","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"T